Banco Santander Totta SA, the
Portuguese unit of  Spain â€™s largest lender, is offering to buy
back three asset-backed securities, according to three people
with knowledge of the offer.  The tender refers to three senior portions of mortgage-
backing securities issued through HipoTotta N.1 Plc., HipoTotta
N.4 Plc., and HipoTotta N. 5 Plc., said the people, who declined
to be identified before the deal is completed. The offering
expires on March 23, the people said.  Santander is managing the tender with Deutsche Bank AG,
